Import data versions

Source: R/importDataVersions.R
importDataVersions.Rd

Import data versions

importDataVersions(file)

Arguments

file

character(1). File path.

Value

DataFrame.

Note

The data_versions.csv file is only generated for special genomes containing additional information (e.g. the built-in "hg38" build).

Updated 2020-01-17.

Author

Michael Steinbaugh

Examples

file <- file.path(bcbioBaseTestsURL, "data-versions.csv")
x <- importDataVersions(file)

#> → Downloading <https://r.acidgenomics.com/testdata/bcbiobase/v0.6/data-versions.csv> to /private/var/folders/l1/8y8sjzmn15v49jgrqglghcfr0000gn/T/RtmpIpeu56/pipette-5d97432d29f2.csv.
#> → Importing pipette-5d97432d29f2.csv at /private/var/folders/l1/8y8sjzmn15v49jgrqglghcfr0000gn/T/RtmpIpeu56 using vroom::`vroom()`.
print(x)

#> DataFrame with 5 rows and 3 columns
#>        genome        resource    version
#>   <character>     <character>  <POSIXct>
#> 1        mm10         sranseq 2015-10-14
#> 2        mm10         srnaseq 2016-11-21
#> 3        mm10 problem_regions 2015-10-28
#> 4        mm10           dbsnp 2013-09-12
#> 5        mm10     transcripts 2014-07-14
